cac:ProcurementProject.cbc:Name: Tender for the provision to establish a panel of Recruitment Representatives for five (5) years duration in relation to International Student Recruitment Services
cac:ProcurementProject.cbc:Description: SETU aims to establish a panel of Recruitment Representatives to assist in recruiting International Students across all its campuses. All applicants who complete the Qualification Questionnaire in Appendix 1, and demonstrate their expertise in this area, will be eligible for consideration for the PANEL. SETU intends to conduct a tender process to engage International Recruitment Representatives. The primary objectives are to ensure value for money, compliance with procurement regulations, uphold ethical recruitment principles (such as the London Principles and the TrustEd International Education Mark) and enhance the process of recruiting international students through overseas Recruitment Representatives. This aims to maximise the number of international students and the associated income stream.
